sentences.sentence: I used to club alone frequently before covid hits.

I just ended a bad relationship and need plenty of alone time to gather or straighten my thoughts.I am more of an introvert/shy guy when I am sober but during these solo drinking/clubbing sessions I realized I can actually start a friendly coversation with tourists or expats.
You know it really just starts from "Do you frequent here?"
or simply "So where are you from?
".For context, I am 193cm tall and relatively well built.
I feel that I can really be myself when I drink/club alone.
You know friends like your typical poly/NS mates will tease or mock you when you try to chat up girls in the club or bar.
And also the fear of embarrassing yourself in front of friends can be quite offputting.
But when you are alone, there is literally nothing to fear.
You are on your own, nobody knows you, it doesnt really matter if you screw up or embarrass yourself.
If you get rejected, just move the hell on.
You still have a full night ahead of you and plenty of people in the club to try socialising.I usually go to the club for the EDM and alcohol, really.
I pretty much enjoy the idea of just myself, EDM and alcohol.
But I am also always getting lucky and scoring home(hotel) runs when I am alone too.
I did ask the girls that I have gotten lucky with, what attracted them to me.
Their response are usually that I am tall, alone and seem to be having a great time.
Probably these are the pointers that girls who can be DTF look out for.

Definitely I also have nights when I just go home alone hahaha but no regrets tho.But the point is, I am comfortable being alone and it can be quite liberating if you can find joy in doing what you like, alone.
It was a good run and I eventually found myself a girlfriend at a club right before covid hit our shores.
We are together for almost 3 years now and probably cant see ourselves in a club before we tie the knots, sadly.PS: I love Swedish House Mafia and a good, stiff whiskey sour.
